The biggest problem with this thread is that people keep changing the reason why they want AD, Grummus, ect. on rotation. First it was about how teaming is unfair to rotation mobs. Then it was about how AD needs a rotation even though there isn't a whole lot competition for the mob. Finially, it was about how we needed it to protect the Rallos Zek rotation.<br>
<br>
<hr></blockquote><!--EZCODE QUOTE END--><br>
<br>
No, the biggest problem is that people keep changing the reason why they want to kill these mobs.  First it was because they didn't want ot waste time doing the alternate quests, now it's for forward preogression, I hear it might also be about loot.  My reasons for being against teaming <!--EZCODE BOLD START--><strong> but not forming an alliance</strong><!--EZCODE BOLD END--> have never changed.  You want guilds A and B to still have 2 sets of loot from trak, and then team up for loot on AD as well.  Meanwhile guild C that is also on trak is also rotating with you for AD.  Merge, make A and B one guild or don't, I don't care, but stop double dipping on the low end content, it's not fair to other people who you are sharing that content with.  This is about double dipping and the reason (spirit) of why you are not allowed to double dip.  Nothing has changed.  The fact that I have to use 20 different illustrations to show the same points just shows that sometimes it takes different things for different people to understand the same point.<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE QUOTE START--><blockquote><strong><em>Quote:</em></strong><hr><br>
Why would anyone care if we let another guild (or a mixture of people) come along and fill up the other 32 spots? Is there a problem getting those 32 people flagged? I can't think of any unselfish reason why anyone would have a problem with this, yet making TT an unneccessary (illegal in my opinion) rotation would prevent this. So instead of helping people out, we let those 32 spots go to waste?<br>
<hr></blockquote><!--EZCODE QUOTE END--><br>
<br>
So you are saying whenever a mob is killed all 72 flags should be used or you are being selfish?  So you are saying people should get something for nothing?  Is that what I am understanding you to mean here?  You want guilds giving away free flags and loot to people who contribute nothing to the fight?  I mean cmon, sharing content is one thing, but I am opposed to a welfare type system in which people just show up for free loot and flags on mobs they CANNOT actually kill.  If your 40 kill it, then another guild kills, and down the road you extend the courtesy of flagging to people who can actually tackle the content I can see your point, otherwise it makes no sense to me at all.  Helping people is one thing on mobs they have proven they can do, but doing it all for them is quite another.<br>
<br>
Rydawg24 feel free to /movelog to a FFA server.  I hear Druzzil is nice this time of year.  On a side note somone was telling me in Serverwide Coercer the other night that they perma cockblock guilds from progressing by killing certain flag mobs.  Other guilds should be into the elementals about this time next year... maybe....  I love how you bitch and moan about how the current system restricts your game play and how much it holds you down.  Be thankful you have 24 hours to kill the mobs you are on rotation for and uber guilds don't dispatch a single group to kill what takes your whole guild to do.  More importantly than that, if you are really after the high end content give up the low end content to those guilds who don't want to team up and actually want that loot<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE QUOTE START--><blockquote><strong><em>Quote:</em></strong><hr><br>
As new guilds are form and progress, they don't learn how the &quot;uber&quot; guilds did many of these &quot;lower content&quot; mobs. They learn how they are done now. Yes, how they are done now may involve teaming up.<br>
<hr></blockquote><!--EZCODE QUOTE END--><br>
<br>
Wow Fitz, you are really missing the boat here.  Guess what no one said you can never ever combine 2 guilds to kill a mob.  However it has always been conditional.  If you team up on one mob team up on <!--EZCODE BOLD START--><strong>ALL</strong><!--EZCODE BOLD END--> mobs.  Please explain to me how this is so restrictive?  Your teaming up is nothing new, what is new is that you now also want NO restrictions on teaming up.  That my friend is utter greed.  Be fair to those who are lesser than your guild(s) and only dip once from the rotations you share with them.  How hard is that to do?<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE QUOTE START--><blockquote><strong><em>Quote:</em></strong><hr><br>
To say what they are doing is wrong is incorrect, becuase to them, it's the accepted way, the traditional way, the way it has been done for the last couple of years.<br>
<hr></blockquote><!--EZCODE QUOTE END--><br>
<br>
To expect that uber guilds won't cockblock you on mobs you want to try or just FFA on the mobs you like to kill rotationally requires that you don't doubel dip.  This is really easy to solve.  Form an <!--EZCODE BOLD START--><strong>ALLIANCE</strong><!--EZCODE BOLD END-->.  Bing bing problem solved, no one will bitch and moan about your two guilds teaming up anymore.  Your desire to reach beyond your grasp while at the same time maintaining total protection is the source of your frustration.  Why do you want to have so much?  Why can't you be fair to the guilds who are smaller than you and take less loot from the mobs you currently share with them?<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE QUOTE START--><blockquote><strong><em>Quote:</em></strong><hr><br>
To expect people to automatically give up what they learn and change and follow your methods is rediculas. Yes, now you must put up with us new guilds, and we must work together to form a system that works for both of us.<br>
<hr></blockquote><!--EZCODE QUOTE END--><br>
<br>
And I learned how to kill Trak with 3 people on the UDB spawned Trak.  You can't possibly expect me to give this up.  Since BotS is a guild of ~ 60 people lets say that safely any given group of 6 BotS could kill him.  You would expect us to get 10 rotations on him then right?  Wrong, we would still only get one, yet you want to take guilds A, B,C and give them 3 kills on him, and then also combine forces to higher end content.  Exactly how is this fair to guilds D, E, and F that you share the Trak rotation with again?  Combine and be one Trak rotation, stop being so greedy.<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE QUOTE START--><blockquote><strong><em>Quote:</em></strong><hr><br>
Where is the compromise? What are the teamers giving to the non-teamers as concession for the ability to team?<br>
<hr></blockquote><!--EZCODE QUOTE END--><br>
<br>
Nothing.  None want to give up anything.  What happens when an unsoppable force hits an immovable object?  The situation we currently have.<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE BOLD START--><strong>SOLUTION</strong><!--EZCODE BOLD END--><br>
<br>
This is my suggestion for a fair comprimise.  Even though I vehemently reject the idea of allowing any sort of teaming without making a formal alliance, it appears as there are those hell bent on throwing the complete system into chaos if they can not have their way.<br>
<br>
I would suggest that guilds that wish to team on higher end content be fair to those who they are currently on rotation with on other mobs and are not teaming.  A good thing to give up would be one complete set of rotations.  IE you autopass all your current rotations one time for each mob you team on.  You team on 4 mobs you skip 4 complete rotations on all mobs.  At it's heart, guilds that are only doing lower end content would get more access to the content they are sharing with teamers.  Teamers get access to more higher end content.  It is simple to administer as far as the current system goes.  It applies the same penalty to all so none can try and scheme their way around it by timing a team kill to just after completeing a heavy set of rotations.  Additionly if it is really that beneficail why do you really need to be killing sev this round.  It would help to mitigate large rotations for those that really do want the &quot;high&quot; end content.<br>
<br>
In addition to this I would suggest that a &quot;team&quot; also not be allowed on to any pop rotation unless they make a formal alliance and merge all rotations.  This would include killing mobs like RZ for flagging.  If a formal alliance was made and the guilds later split individually, they would be required to back kill all flag mobs before being considered for elemental rotations etc... as the now single entities.<br>
<br>
Last thing would be guilds that try to hide their teaming by not posting it and hoping no one will find out.  A penalty of 2 passes on all rotations as a penalty for not announcing your teaming kills.  Basically you get 2x's the penalty for trying to avoid it all together.<br>
<br>
This to me is a fair comprimise.  It carries a fairly heafty downside to it, however the plus side is that if you are going after elementals, do you really need Trak, Sev, KT etc... ?  I mean cmon, free up these rotations for the small guilds who really do need this loot.  Be fair to those less than you.  This isn't an argument about uber verses mid sized guilds.  This is a debate over weather or not mid sized guilds are being fair to guilds BOTH smaller and larger than them respectively by teaming but not forming an alliance.  The real plus side is that if you team you don't get booted off all rotations and have to re-enter them.  So if you decide that teaming isn't your thing a few months down the road the penalty is much much less than the dissolving of a formal alliance.<br>
<br>
-Regards<br>
