<br>
I've been aiding the anti-team movement in explaining their point of view, but now allow be to share with you the problem.<br>
<br>
The problem is that is doesn't matter if Karadin, Gromm, Gradukk, Rogg, or whomever else see AD, Grummus, TT, MB as &quot;rotation mobs&quot;, worthy of the same discipline and rules as mobs that are currently on the page.<br>
<br>
You know why it doesn't matter?  Because according to the written rules, ANYBODY CAN TEAM UP ON ANY MOB IN THE GAME THAT THEY WANT TO, WITH NO PENALTY, AS LONG AS THE MOBS NAME DOES NOT APPEAR ON THE <!--EZCODE BOLD START--><strong><!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><em><!--EZCODE UNDERLINE START--><span style="text-decoration:underline">ROTATIONS PAGE</span><!--EZCODE UNDERLINE END--></em><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--></strong><!--EZCODE BOLD END-->.<br>
<br>
You guys want to bitch and moan about &quot;blah blah blah it's a technicality&quot;, and threaten everyone with putting the mobs on rotation.  Who gives a crap?  Put the mobs on rotation if thats what you want.<br>
<br>
SHIT, OR GET OFF THE POT.<br>
<br>
I'm tired of listening to this banter go back and forth because nobody wants to &quot;cockblock&quot;.  Stop trying to be politically correct and choose between one of two choices.<br>
<br>
1.  Put the mobs on rotation and end this discussion.<br>
2.  Admit that you don't care enough about them to police teaming.<br>
<br>
There have been no acceptable alternatives to the solution.<br>
<br>
Last night, me and the rest of the ST keyed members of Shadows of Yamabushi attempted to get on the Sleeper's Tomb Ancients Rotation.  According to the rules as they were posted, we were allowed to do that.<br>
<br>
Come to find out today that the rulemakers MEANT to put in a rule about only being able to do that on your regular ST Rotation.  Well shit, our bad.  But guess what?  They realized that it wasn't part of the rules and fixed it, IN WRITING.<br>
<br>
What that means is that anybody can team on any mob that isn't on the Rotations PAGE, any time they want, and not suffer any physical penalties.<br>
<br>
Do you want that to change?<br>
<br>
Then make a rule or put them on rotation.<br>
<br>
Until then, STOP with the speculative banter, and crazy non-rule spin.<br>
<br>
