Have you actually read any of the responses?  You want to team up?  Fine, no one objects to that.  Many people have already said alliances are just peachy and is actually covered under current rotation rules.  The rule being, once you form an alliance, you are treated as a single entity for all rotation mobs and cannot pick and choose mobs you want to stay a single entity for and allied for others.  Which sounds imminently fair to me.  If it doesn't, ask yourself how your actions impact the up and coming guilds such as VoF and LoM, not the uberguilds, and who exactly is the greedy party here?<br>
<br>
[quote] There is a source of friction here though. Many of these "new" guilds aren't so new any more and maybe they are now competing with some of the "uber" guilds. [/quote]<br>
