<br>
I'll just cite Tunare as an example.  The original Tunare that BotS killed was the size of a regular high elf and had the hit box of one, which made MTing incredibly difficult what with her DD-knockback-root proc and inability for any single tank to maintain aggro and expose the tiny hitbox behind her to the rest of the raid.  Typically when you cornered her, her proc would fling you off the wall and land you behind her, rooted, and there went her exposed back for the rest of the guild.  Trying her Dain style just got clerics summoned and killed and the rest of the raid in short order.  To say the current Tunare encounter is &quot;gimped&quot; is almost an understatement.<br>
<br>
In closing, I would just like to add that I don't see how changing/abolishing the rotation system will adversely affect the uberguilds.  The uberguilds have enjoyed peace and harmony here on Rathe that is almost unheard of on any other servers and I think they will quite happily keep the rotation system as is for the mobs they are interested in.  And from what I've read, the vast majority of the Rathe community seems happy with the rotation rules as is as well.  If you are so unhappy with the current system, server transfer is always an option.<br>
